full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/25/2023 HKC-223 TO BE COMPLETED BY APPLICANT REQUESTING EXTENSION OF REENTRY PERMIT 1. Do. you or your spouse own a home or apartment in a foreign country? Yes No If yes, date purchased: march 1977 2. Do you or your spouse own real estate in the United States? Yes No 3. If you are married, is your spouse a: lawful permanent resident of U.S. U.S. citizen, Passport No. local resident Visa Petition submitted for spouse. Visa Petition not submitted for spouse. 4. Have you or your spouse been employed abroad? Yes No If yes, by whom: employed by a local company self-employed employed by U.S. Company 5. What close relatives do you have in the United States? Spouse Children Parents 6. When and where were you admitted to the United States for permanent residence? Date: Mary 30,1973 Port of Entry: Hawaii 7. How many Reentry Permits have been issued to you: One Two Three or more 8. Attach a copy of your U.S. income tax return, Form 1040, for the past calender year. If you failed to file Form 1040, explain below: I certify that I know the contents of this questionaire signed by me and that all statements are true and correct.
